      "text": [
        " : سُئِلَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ شَرِيكَيْنِ شَهِدَ أَحَدُهُمَا لِصَاحِبِهِ قَالَ \"تَجُوزُ شَهَادَتُهُ إِلاَّ فِي شَيْءٍ لَهُ فِيهِ نَصِيبٌ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3293 - And Fadalah narrated from Aban, who said:\nAbu Abdullah (as), was asked about two partners, one of whom testified for the other.\nImam (as) said: \"His testimony is valid except in something where he has a share.\""
        ]
      }
